register.description: This register contains the IP revision code for the PRM part of the PRCM

This register provides status on MPU interrupt events. Any event is logged independently of the corresponding IRQENABLE value. SW is required to clear a set bit by writing a '1' into the bit-position to be cleared.

bitfield.description: IVA ABB mode change completion status. This status is set for both automatic transition upon a voltage transition, and OPP change (when OPP_CHANGE bit is cleared by hardware in PRM_ABBLDO_MM_CTRL register). It is cleared by SW.

DSPEVE ABB mode change completion status. This status is set for both automatic transition upon a voltage transition, and OPP change (when OPP_CHANGE bit is cleared by hardware in PRM_ABBLDO_MM_CTRL register). It is cleared by SW.

GPU ABB mode change completion status. This status is set for both automatic transition upon a voltage transition, and OPP change (when OPP_CHANGE bit is cleared by hardware in PRM_ABBLDO_MM_CTRL register). It is cleared by SW.

Software supervised transition completed event interrupt status (any domain). Asserted upon completion of any clock domain force wakeup transition or upon completion of any power domain sleep transition with at least one enclosed clock domain configured in forced-sleep.

register.description: This register is used to configure the PRM's 32-bit debug output. There is one 7-bit source select field for selecting from a shared set of 8-bit internal signal blocks per byte. The signals included in each block are specified in the PRCM integration specification. [warm reset insensitive]

bitfield.description: Internal signal block select for debug word byte-1
